        // We only need to check substrings where the binary value is not too large.
        // The maximum length is n. So f(s_l...s_r) <= n.
        // A binary string of length K has value at most 2^K - 1.
        // If K is around 20, 2^20 is about 10^6, which is > n.
        // So we only need to consider substrings of length up to about 20-21 characters after the first '1'.
