    int q = p; // Start from where the non-decreasing suffix ended
    while (q > 0 && a[q-1] <= a[q]) {
        q--;
    }
    // Now a[q...n-1] is a "good" suffix.
    // The elements a[q...p-1] are non-increasing, and a[p...n-1] are non-decreasing.
    // This means a[q] >= a[q+1] >= ... >= a[p-1] and a[p] <= a[p+1] <= ... <= a[n-1].
    // The overall structure is a peak or valley, or just monotonic.
    // The elements a[q...n-1] can be sorted by picking from ends.
