        //     Let O(x) be the coins Opponent gets if it's Chanek's turn with x coins.
        //     C(x) + O(x) = x.
        //     If Chanek takes N/2, then Opponent plays on N/2.
        //     Opponent will get C(N/2) from the remaining N/2.
        //     So Chanek gets N/2 + (N/2 - C(N/2)).
        //     This is N - C(N/2).

