        // C(N) = max( 1 + (N-1 - C_opp(N-1)), N/2 + (N/2 - C_opp(N/2)) )
        // C_opp(x) is the coins Chanek gets if it's Opponent's turn with x coins.
        // C_opp(x) = x - C(x).
        // So C(N) = max( 1 + (N-1 - (N-1 - C(N-1))), N/2 + (N/2 - (N/2 - C(N/2))) )
        // C(N) = max( 1 + C(N-1), N/2 + C(N/2) )
        // This is not quite right. C(N-1) is Chanek's score if Chanek starts with N-1.
